# Content Engine â€“ Product Roadmap
_Last updated: YYYY-MM-DD_

This roadmap outlines the planned evolution of the Content Engine from the current MVP toward a production-grade, enterprise-deployable platform. It integrates all architecture, UX, feature, and future-capability discussions to date.

---

# 1. ğŸ¯ Vision & Objectives

The Content Engine enables users to:
- Upload or provide sources (documents, pasted text, URLs)
- Generate structured investment-grade written outputs
- Apply defined style guides and scenario rules
- Produce public-facing vs complete/internal versions
- Iterate via rewrite instructions
- Track version history with metadata and scoring
- Provide transparency through source auditability and statement reliability

Future goals:
- Real public-domain retrieval
- Internal knowledge-base ingestion
- Document similarity checks
- Multi-client style guide switching
- Enterprise-grade privacy, access control, and SSO
- Automated templated Word/PPT outputs

---

# 2. â­ Completed (MVP Foundations)

### 2.1 Core Features
- Upload & parse text, files, and URLs
- Scenario-based prompt templates
- Complete vs Public-facing drafting
- Inline style guide compliance
- Version generation and rewrite
- Token, temperature, model selection

### 2.2 UI/UX
- Full UI overhaul (2025)
- Cleaner layout and spacing
- Collapsible advanced settings
- Color-coded metadata pills
- Consistent controls + button hierarchy
- Sources table (user-provided)

### 2.3 Reliability & Debugging
- CORS overhaul & correct headers
- Backend restructuring and cleanup
- Removal of circular imports
- Safe JSON parsing
- Stable scoring engine
- Error toasts with safe truncation

---

# 3. ğŸ›  In Progress (Actively Being Implemented)

### 3.1 Statement Reliability (Beta)
- New backend endpoint `/api/analyse-statements`
- Break draft into atomic statements
- Reliability scoring (0â€“100%)
- Classification:
  - Source-based factual
  - Plausible factual
  - Interpretive/subjective
  - Speculative/forward-looking
- Flags for risks (e.g., â€œnot supported by sourceâ€)
- UI table under Draft card

### 3.2 Style Guide Consolidation
- One location only: `DEFAULT_STYLE_GUIDE`
- Rules for:
  - Numbers (â€œoneâ€â€“â€œelevenâ€, ranges, units)
  - No em-dashes
  - Institutional tone
  - Currency handling
  - Paragraph structure
- Removal of duplicated rules from prompts

### 3.3 Source Snapshot Per Version
- Every generated/rewrite version stores:
  - File names, size
  - URLs
  - Text-length metrics
- Displayed in Sources table

