# 4. ğŸ§© Next Up (Short-Term Roadmap)

### 4.1 Full Public-Source Retrieval (Real Web Context)
(Currently, public search = â€œallow model knowledgeâ€. Next version = real retrieval.)

#### Backend
- `/api/public-search` endpoint
- Connect to a real web search service (Google Custom Search, Bing Search, Tavily, Perplexity, etc.)
- Extract canonical URLs, titles, snippets
- Provide structured `publicSources` list
- Prevent hallucinated URLs

#### Frontend
- Merge `userProvidedSources` + `publicSources`
- Expanded Sources table:
  - File / URL / Text / Public Web Source
- Optional: relevance ranking

---

### 4.2 Rewrite Consistency Improvements
- Allow version-type switching mid-version
- Preview changes before committing rewrite
- Rewrite-specific word limit override (optional)

---

### 4.3 Source Management UX
- â€œRemove sourceâ€ (X button) for uploaded files & URLs
- â€œPreview sourceâ€ inspector pane
- Show count of total uploaded sources
- Confirmation dialogs before removing big files

---

### 4.4 Prompt Audit Mode (Light)
- Show â€œeffective promptâ€ for transparency
- User toggle: display prompt or hide
- Stripped of internal logic (safe mode)

